><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jtr1665702874645.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jtr1665702874645.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jtr1665702874645.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jtr1665702874645\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface Support for Unicode\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__uniface_support_for_unicode_92658\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface supports Unicode in the user interface, database storage and retrieval, sorting, case conversion, and data exchange. Uniface uses Unicode UTF-8 encoding for as its internal character set.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__p_d28181e1_d28182e1_d28183e1\">On GUI platforms, any Unicode characters can appear in the user interface, and be entered into String fields. On any Uniface-supported platform, Unicode characters can be stored in and retrieved from a Unicode-supported database, and exchanged with other Unicode-based components, such as Java and Unicode files.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__p_d28184e1_d28185e1_d28186e1\">Uniface also supports Unicode sorting, case conversion (sometimes known as bending), and normalization, making it possible to sort and search strings based on the current locale. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fjz1665702531973.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fjz1665702531973.html\" title=\"The language of an application is associated not only with a character set, but with regional conventions for sorting, for expressing numbers, currency, date and time, and so on. The combination of language and region is known as locale.\">Language and Locale</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__p_d28187e1_d28188e1_d28189e1\">Uniface uses Unicode UTF-8 encoding for as its internal character set. However, Uniface does not provide the glyphs to display the characters, nor does it supply the tools to enter the characters. These are handled by Microsoft Windows.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__p_d28190e1_d28191e1_d28192e1\">For data entry and display, Microsoft Windows must be configured to display and input the desired Unicode characters, and Uniface must be configured to use a Unicode Font for displaying Unicode characters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__p_d28193e1_d28194e1_d28195e1\">To develop and deploy a Unicode application in Uniface, you need to understand the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__li_d14423e1_d14424e1_d14425e1\">The correct data type and packing code for storing Unicode characters\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__li_d14426e1_d14427e1_d14428e1\">Where Unicode characters are allowed and where not\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jtr1665702874645__li_d14429e1_d14430e1_d14431e1\">ProcScript functions that can handle Unicode characters\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529045\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529045\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Support for Unicode Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Support for Unicode Uniface supports Unicode in the user interface, database storage and retrieval, sorting, case conversion, and data exchange. Uniface uses Unicode UTF-8 encoding for as its internal character set. On GUI platforms, any Unicode characters can appear in the user interface, and be entered into String fields. On any Uniface-supported platform, Unicode characters can be stored in and retrieved from a Unicode-supported database, and exchanged with other Unicode-based components, such as Java and Unicode files. Uniface also supports Unicode sorting, case conversion (sometimes known as bending), and normalization, making it possible to sort and search strings based on the current locale. For more information, see Language and Locale . Uniface uses Unicode UTF-8 encoding for as its internal character set. However, Uniface does not provide the glyphs to display the characters, nor does it supply the tools to enter the characters. These are handled by Microsoft Windows. For data entry and display, Microsoft Windows must be configured to display and input the desired Unicode characters, and Uniface must be configured to use a Unicode Font for displaying Unicode characters. To develop and deploy a Unicode application in Uniface, you need to understand the following: The correct data type and packing code for storing Unicode characters Where Unicode characters are allowed and where not ProcScript functions that can handle Unicode characters Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}